      "writtenOn": "2017-03-23T17:28:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I suggest that the SkColorSetARGB() macro be the canonical way to construct a SkColor from four numbers.  We don\u0027t need to document the internal structure of SkColor if we just tell users to always use SkColorSetARGB and SkColorGet{A,R,G,B}.\n\nQuestion:  should we have a pointer to colorspace/gamut documentation here?  Is the paint\u0027s color relative to the surface\u0027s colorspace?   Is this the same or different for a SkColorShader",
      "revId": "5422c8b84d756a644b71c5c8bd72fddfe7a6b5fc",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "34f85473_00eabafb",
        "filename": "experimental/docs/paint.bmh",
        "patchSetId": 16
      },
      "lineNbr": 1958,
      "author": {
        "id": 5632
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-03-23T18:38:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I would counter-argue that if \nsetColor(0xFF00FF00) is acceptable, then it is also acceptable to document the SkColor format.\n\nI\u0027m a long way from documenting color, but I would further argue that the concepts of conical source color formats and device-dependent color formats are not intuitive and deserve thorough documentation.\n\nYes, there should be a  #SeeAlso to #Topic Color_Space. I hope that the paint color is always treated identically to a shader -- e.g., a linear gradient with a single color should draw identically to a paint\u0027s color.",
      "parentUuid": "ff8a2911_19f5b6d1",
      "revId": "5422c8b84d756a644b71c5c8bd72fddfe7a6b5fc",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
